title: Breaking News BREAKING: Police say 2 bodies found in Moncrief area on Saturday Learn More
content: The Jacksonville Sheriff’s Office found two bodies Saturday in the Moncrief area.    JSO reported an undetermined death in the area of West 31st Street and Stuart Street, as well as another body found in 13th and Moncrief Road.    Those bodies found are miles apart from each other, so it's currently unclear if they are related or not.      We’re responding to two scenes of undetermined deaths off of Moncrief Rd. this afternoon. These photos are from West 13th. We have another crew a few blocks away at West 31st. We’ll have the latest on both at 6 and 6:30 on @FCN2go  pic.twitter.com/EjdsyCp2fk  — Julia Jenaé (@JuliaJenaeFCN) June 2, 2018    So far no information regarding those two people has been released to the media.    Stay with First Coast News as we continue to follow this developing story.    © 2018 WTLV
